r of the world |work=Telegraph |date=December 7, 2002 |accessdate=2010-03-05}}</ref> * The [[Church of Saint George, Lalibela|rock-hewn churches]] at [[Lalibela]], [[Ethiopia]]<ref>[https://www.theguardian.com/world/2014/sep/01/ethiopia-rock-churches-tourism-lalibela Ancient rock churches put Ethiopia back on tourist map] by David Smith, ''[[The Guardian]]'', September 1, 2014.</ref> (Church of Saint George, Lalibela) * [[Royal Palace (Amsterdam)|Royal Palace in Amsterdam]], [[Netherlands]]<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.bma.amsterdam.nl/adam/uk/groot/paleis.html|title=Amsterdam Heritage: Town hall in the Dam Square (1648/65), now Royal Palace|website=Municipal Department for Preservation and Restoration of Historic Buildings and Sites of Amsterdam|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20060505121746/http://www.bma.amsterdam.nl/adam/uk/groot/paleis.html|archivedate=2006-05-05|df=}}</ref> * [[Sigiriya]], [[Sri Lanka]]<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.tribuneindia.com/2003/20030810/spectrum/travel.htm |title=Pearl of the Indian Ocean|author=Singh, Priyanka |location=Chandigarh|work=[[The Tribune (Chandigarh)|The Tribune]]|date= August 10, 2003}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.dailynews.lk/2004/01/01/fea15.html|title=Tourist miracles of Sri Lanka|author=Moin-ul-Haq|work=[[Daily News (Sri Lanka)|Daily News]]|location=Sri Lanka|date=January 1, 2004|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20061008192253/http://www.dailynews.lk/2004/01/01/fea15.html|archivedate=October 8, 2006|df=}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.deccanherald.com/deccanherald/aug152004/sh4.asp|title=Breathtaking castle in the sky|author=Belliappa, C.P.|work=[[Deccan Herald]]|date=August 15, 2004|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20060524125745/http://www.deccanherald.com/deccanherald/aug152004/sh4.asp|archivedate=May 24, 2006|df=}}</ref> * [[Statue of Liberty]], [[New York Harbor]], [[United States]]<ref>{{cite news|url=https://query.nytimes.com/search/query?frow=0&n=10&srcht=s&daterange=period&query=%22Statue+of+Liberty%22+%22wonder+of+the+world%22&srchst=p&hdlquery=&bylquery=&mon1=09&day1=18&year1=1851&mon2=12&day2=31&year2=1980&submit.x=14&submit.y=13 |title= Archive Search for 'Statue of Liberty wonder of the world' |work=New York Times |date= |accessdate=2010-03-05}}</ref> * [[Stonehenge]], [[United Kingdom]]<ref>{{cite web|url=http://uk.toluna.com/polls/15449/The_Eighth_Wonder_of_the_World%3F |title=The Eighth Wonder of the World? &#124; Toluna |website=Uk.toluna.com |date= |accessdate=2010-03-05}}</ref> * The [[Taj Mahal]], [[India]]<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.tajmahaltourism.com/about-tajmahal/index.html |date=December 1, 2007 |website=Taj Majal Tourism |title=Index |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20071201131515/http://www.tajmahaltourism.com/about-tajmahal/index.html |archivedate=December 1, 2007 |df= }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.soygrowers.com/library/india/images4.htm |date=October 25, 2007 |website=soygrowers.com |title=Images 4 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20071025041057/http://www.soygrowers.com/library/india/images4.htm |archivedate=October 25, 2007 |df= }}</ref> * The [[Terracotta Army]], [[China]]<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.dreamxian.com/tour-xian-2/introduction-of-terracotta-army-the-eighth-wonder-of-the-world.html |website=dreamxian.com |title=Introduction of the Terracotta Army, the Eighth Wonder of the World |date=September 6, 2012 |deadurl=bot: unknown |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120906041521/http://www.dreamxian.com/tour-xian-2/introduction-of-terracotta-army-the-eighth-wonder-of-the-world.html |archivedate=September 6, 2012 |df= }}</ref> * The original rail-only [[Victoria Bridge (Montreal)]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.nfb.ca/film/victoria_bridge_the_8th_wonder |title=''Victoria Bridge: The 8th Wonder''&nbsp;– a National Film Board of Canada short|website=nfb.ca}}</ref>
===Post-1900 creations=== * [[Aswan Dam]] in Egypt, called as such by [[Nikita Khrushchev]]<ref>{{cite news|last1=Walz|first1=Jay|title=Khrushchev and Nasser Join In Diverting the Nile at Aswan|url=https://www.nytimes.com/1964/05/15/khrushchev-and-nasser-join-in-diverting-the-nile-at-a-swan.html|accessdate=31 January 2018|work=New York Times|date=May 15, 1964|page=1}}</ref> * [[Terraces (Bahá'í)|Bahá'í terraces]], on [[Mount Carmel, Israel|Mount Carmel]], [[Haifa]], [[Israel]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.israel-mfa.gov.il/MFA/Israel%20beyond%20the%20conflict/The%20Eighth%20Wonder%20of%20the%20World%20-%20In%20Haifa|date= July 2001 |title= The 'Eighth Wonder of the World' – in Haifa |website=Israel-mfa.gov.il |accessdate=2013-01-18}}</ref> * [[Delta Works]], the [[Netherlands|Dutch]] provinces of [[Zeeland]] and [[Zuid-Holland]], the [[Netherlands]]. The Delta Works has been called one of the [[Seven Wonders of the Modern World]] by ''Quest'' magazine and the American Society of Civil Engineers, and the "Eighth Wonder of the World" by several other sources.<ref>{{cite news | title=Deltawerken | date = 2011-03-26 | url=http://www.vvvzeeland.nl/en/about-zeeland/delta-works | work=VVVZeeland | accessdate=2011-11-20}}</ref> [[File:Sydney opera house side view.jpg|thumb|[[Sydney Opera House]], [[Sydney]], Australia]] * [[Empire State Building]], [[New York City]].<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.esbnyc.com/kids/index.cfm |title=Empire State Building official site |website=Esbnyc.com |date= |accessdate=2013-01-18 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130629064031/http://www.esbnyc.com/kids/index.cfm |archivedate=2013-06-29 |df= }}</ref><ref>[http://journalism.nyu.edu/pubzone/ripples/feature_skaroff.html "Does Extra Security Make it Safe?"] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20060110013403/http://www.journalism.nyu.edu/pubzone/ripples/feature_skaroff.html |date=2006-01-10 }} by Rebecca Skaroff, ''Ripples'', [[New York University]].</ref> * [[Great Manmade River]] in Libya; given the title by Muammar Gaddafi.<ref>{{cite web|title=GMR (Great Man-made River) Water Supply Project|url=http://www.water-technology.net/projects/gmr/|website=Net Resources International|accessdate=26 October 2011}}</ref> * [[Hibernia Gravity Base Structure|Hibernia Oil Platform]]<ref>{{cite web|title=Interesting Facts about Oil and Gas|url=http://www.petrogenltd.com/2016/01/22/interesting-facts-about-oil-and-gas/|website=PetroGEN|accessdate=15 November 2017}}</ref> * [[Houston Astrodome]]<ref>{{cite news | first=Chris | last=Duncan | title=Historic Astrodome sits empty, awaits future | date = 2011-03-26 | url=http://www.denverpost.com/rockies/ci_17708291 | work=The Denver Post | accessdate=2011-11-20}}</ref> * [[International Space Station]] in Orbit around Earth; title given by the Americans and Russians.{{citation needed||date=January 2014}} * [[Karakoram Highway]] in [[Pakistan]], and [[China]] * [[Palm Islands]] of [[Dubai]]<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.iea.org.uk/record.jsp?ID=338&type=news |title=The lessons of Dubai? Let’s build some more British isles |author=Blundell, John |website=[[Institute of Economic Affairs]] |date=April 9, 2006 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20060507085656/http://www.iea.org.uk/record.jsp?type=news&ID=338 |archivedate=May 7, 2006 |df= }}</ref> * [[Panama Canal]]<ref>{{cite book | last1=Soley | title=Culture and Customs of Panama | url=https://books.google.com/books?id=cNEcEyZs254C&pg=PA86&dq=%22panama+canal%22+%22eighth+wonder%22&hl=en&ei=kN7ITuCkGcng0QHJ2JER&sa=X&oi=book_result&ct=result&resnum=2&ved=0CDgQ6AEwATgK#v=onepage&q=%22panama%20canal%22%20%22eighth%20wonder%22&f=false | accessdate=2011-11-20 | isbn=978-0-313-33667-6}}</ref> * [[Pikeville Cut-Through]] in [[Pikeville, Kentucky]]; given the title by ''[[The New York Times]]''.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.tourpikecounty.com/index.php?n=2&id=2 |title=Pikeville Cut-Through|website= Pikeville-Pike County Tourism|access-